WEBVTT

00:06.789 --> 00:09.313
male narrator: Previously,
on "Briarpatch"...

00:09.357 --> 00:11.054
- Why are you in my dead
sister's apartment?

00:11.098 --> 00:12.316
- I'm just looking
for my bug!

00:12.360 --> 00:14.449
- Who paid you?
- Ferness.

00:14.492 --> 00:17.147
- Floyd Ferness.
- Felicity's boyfriend.

00:17.191 --> 00:18.714
- She was on to something.

00:18.757 --> 00:21.151
Okay, something big.

00:21.195 --> 00:23.023
- After this week's
double car bombings...

00:23.066 --> 00:24.111
[explosions boom]

00:24.154 --> 00:25.112
We are declaring a manhunt

00:25.155 --> 00:27.027
for Floyd Ferness.

00:27.070 --> 00:28.245
- I can't protect you

00:28.289 --> 00:29.420
if you don't
give me something.

00:29.464 --> 00:32.032
- Can't nobody protect me now.

00:32.075 --> 00:33.076
- One wonders, though.

00:33.120 --> 00:34.643
Jake Spivey is ready to fulfill

00:34.686 --> 00:35.818
his half of the bargain.

00:35.861 --> 00:37.428
- He won't talk
until we have Brattle.

00:37.472 --> 00:39.039
- If he's not willing to tie

00:39.082 --> 00:40.170
those millions
of missing dollars

00:40.214 --> 00:41.476
around Brattle's neck,

00:41.519 --> 00:43.652
it's no concern of ours
if Spivey's taken out.

00:43.695 --> 00:45.436
- Ever heard of Al-Namur?

00:45.480 --> 00:48.091
Jake has done
some terrible things,

00:48.135 --> 00:50.180
and I can prove them all.

00:50.224 --> 00:51.573
- I know you.

00:51.616 --> 00:53.531
You're my husband's
dead fiancée's sister.

00:53.575 --> 00:56.012
- Your man, Strucker,
did he have family?

00:56.056 --> 00:57.057
- He's got a wife.

00:57.100 --> 00:59.146
I expect she's with him now.

01:00.930 --> 01:03.846
[machine beeping]

01:06.457 --> 01:09.765
[indistinct talking over PA]

01:10.940 --> 01:13.856
[labored breathing]

01:21.168 --> 01:25.607
[beeping grows louder]

01:26.956 --> 01:29.915
[suspenseful music]

01:29.959 --> 01:32.396
♪

01:32.440 --> 01:35.095
- Several animals, including
the fearsome jungle cat,

01:35.138 --> 01:36.531
remain unaccounted for.

01:36.574 --> 01:38.881
[indistinct talking over PA]

01:38.924 --> 01:40.622
In other news,
the funeral service

01:40.665 --> 01:42.972
for fallen San Bonifacio
homicide detective

01:43.015 --> 01:43.973
Felicity Dill

01:44.016 --> 01:45.192
is set to take place

01:45.235 --> 01:46.889
at Trinity Baptist Church
today.

01:46.932 --> 01:50.022
The 28-year-old hero died
as a result of a car bombing.

01:50.066 --> 01:51.502
- Thanks, Ginger.

01:51.546 --> 01:54.418
We'll have more updates
on this story as we--

01:54.462 --> 01:57.856
- The following resulted
in significant injuries.

01:57.900 --> 01:59.119
Cody is in what we call...

01:59.162 --> 02:01.469
[vending machine buzzing]

02:01.512 --> 02:03.601
Uh, to his head
and his extremities,

02:03.645 --> 02:05.125
have left his brain scarred...

02:05.168 --> 02:07.127
- [sobbing]
- Oxygen.

02:07.170 --> 02:08.606
We are, unfortunately...

02:08.650 --> 02:12.175
uh, running a little low on his
blood type, so...

02:12.219 --> 02:14.525
- [sighs]

02:14.569 --> 02:17.702
[light acoustic music]

02:17.746 --> 02:24.666
♪

02:50.213 --> 02:52.302
- [under breath]
Oh, no...

02:52.346 --> 02:59.483
♪

03:01.398 --> 03:04.532
[machine beeping]

03:08.318 --> 03:10.886
[muttering indistinctly]

03:14.411 --> 03:17.849
[tires squealing]

03:17.893 --> 03:20.809
[upbeat dramatic music]

03:20.852 --> 03:27.772
♪

03:41.308 --> 03:44.354
[laughs]

03:44.398 --> 03:50.926
♪

03:52.057 --> 03:53.276
[screams]

03:53.320 --> 03:54.234
[brakes screeching]

03:54.277 --> 03:55.278
[horn honks]

03:55.322 --> 03:57.715
[screaming]

04:06.898 --> 04:08.813
- The manhunt
for double bombing suspect

04:08.857 --> 04:10.641
Floyd Ferness
continues to escalate.

04:10.685 --> 04:11.947
Once a hometown hero,

04:11.990 --> 04:13.383
Ferness is considered
to be armed

04:13.427 --> 04:14.863
and extremely dangerous.

04:20.434 --> 04:23.915
[funky music]

04:23.959 --> 04:27.092
[Sharon Jones & the Dap Kings'
"Just Give Me Your Time"]

04:27.136 --> 04:30.400
♪

04:30.444 --> 04:33.229
[singer vocalizing]

04:33.273 --> 04:36.450
♪

04:36.493 --> 04:38.930
[phone ringing]

04:38.974 --> 04:40.845
- [moans]

04:43.021 --> 04:45.285
[phone ringing]

04:48.418 --> 04:50.202
- Yes?

04:50.246 --> 04:52.596
- Imagine walking
through a dark tunnel,

04:52.640 --> 04:54.294
and there's a tightness
in your stomach

04:54.337 --> 04:55.991
you can't seem to shake.

04:57.166 --> 04:58.472
- Floyd?

04:58.515 --> 05:01.039
- A square light appears
at the end of that tunnel.

05:01.083 --> 05:02.737
You walk towards it.

05:02.780 --> 05:05.783
Tightness increases,
and you step through.

05:05.827 --> 05:07.089
Look up.

05:08.917 --> 05:11.093
You're in the middle
of a packed stadium.

05:11.136 --> 05:14.183
It's your first pro game.
You made it.

05:14.226 --> 05:16.359
The crowd cheers.

05:16.403 --> 05:18.622
Applause echoes like thunder.

05:18.666 --> 05:20.145
You line up
behind the quarterback.

05:20.189 --> 05:21.321
The play is called.

05:21.364 --> 05:24.019
The ball is in your hands.

05:24.062 --> 05:27.327
The only thing left to do now
is the thing you do best.

05:27.370 --> 05:28.371
Run.

05:28.415 --> 05:29.894
[lid pops]
- Mm.

05:29.938 --> 05:32.375
- And then suddenly,
you hear something different.

05:32.419 --> 05:33.855
Pop!

05:35.987 --> 05:38.947
You look down.
You're not running anymore.

05:38.990 --> 05:39.904
You're falling.

05:41.689 --> 05:43.734
It wasn't my knee
got wrecked that day.

05:45.519 --> 05:47.347
It was my whole damn life.

05:47.390 --> 05:48.391
- Jesus Christ, Floyd.

05:48.435 --> 05:50.001
I had a headache
before you called.

05:50.045 --> 05:51.307
[can clanks]

05:51.351 --> 05:53.396
- It's not fair.

05:53.440 --> 05:56.356
What?
That you got hurt?

05:57.879 --> 06:01.273
It could have been
your last game anyway.

06:01.317 --> 06:04.755
You could've got cut.

06:04.799 --> 06:08.019
A sinkhole could've
swallowed the stadium.

06:08.063 --> 06:10.500
Shit happens, Floyd.

06:10.544 --> 06:12.328
You're not special.

06:12.372 --> 06:14.199
- Felicity thought
I was special.

06:14.243 --> 06:15.940
- She thought you were a creep.

06:15.984 --> 06:18.856
She had a secret apartment
so she could hide from you.

06:18.900 --> 06:21.511
You found it and you had
Harold Snow bug her.

06:21.555 --> 06:23.208
- I loved her.

06:23.252 --> 06:25.863
- Honestly, Floyd, it just
sounds like she dumped you.

06:25.907 --> 06:28.736
- You know what still
haunts me?

06:28.779 --> 06:32.566
You'd think it would be
the sound in my knee, but it...

06:32.609 --> 06:35.438
it's the silence,

06:35.482 --> 06:37.092
in the stadium.

06:37.135 --> 06:38.833
[wind howling]

06:38.876 --> 06:40.487
They knew,

06:40.530 --> 06:42.184
before I did.

06:44.229 --> 06:45.970
They all knew it was over.

06:49.278 --> 06:51.715
You ever have that?

06:51.759 --> 06:54.326
A moment you can't
come back from?

06:54.370 --> 06:57.895
- [sighs] It's not too late
for you, Floyd.

06:57.939 --> 07:01.203
You can still do something
for her.

07:01.246 --> 07:03.379
Tell me what's on the tape.

07:03.423 --> 07:05.120
- [sighs]

07:06.600 --> 07:09.211
♪

07:09.254 --> 07:10.865
- Floyd?

07:12.649 --> 07:14.434
[phone cracks]

07:14.477 --> 07:15.826
Floyd?

07:18.176 --> 07:20.135
Floyd?
God damn it.

07:22.050 --> 07:24.095
[sighs]

07:24.139 --> 07:26.097
Clyde Brattle picked me up
last night,

07:26.141 --> 07:27.577
took me for a ride.

07:27.621 --> 07:29.971
I don't know, Cyrus,
a camper van.

07:30.014 --> 07:32.887
I'm fine.
Thanks for asking.

07:32.930 --> 07:35.803
[voice speaking indistinctly]

07:35.846 --> 07:39.328
Not over the phone.
Meet me.

07:39.371 --> 07:41.069
Yes.
I'll find the time.

07:41.112 --> 07:42.636
[elevator dings]

07:42.679 --> 07:45.639
[funky music]

07:45.682 --> 07:47.423
♪

07:47.467 --> 07:49.469
Nope.

07:49.512 --> 07:52.167
I have nothing better
to do today.

07:52.210 --> 07:54.430
♪

07:54.474 --> 07:55.910
[sighs]

07:57.477 --> 07:59.609
♪

08:01.611 --> 08:04.135
- Miss Dill!

08:04.179 --> 08:05.702
I am Sergeant Henry Mock,

08:05.746 --> 08:08.705
and welcome to your chariot
for the day,

08:08.749 --> 08:12.492
courtesy of the San Bonifacio
Police Department.

08:12.535 --> 08:14.624
We heard you don't drive.

08:14.668 --> 08:16.191
- [sighs]
I don't.

08:16.234 --> 08:18.106
- Aces!
I do.

08:18.149 --> 08:20.325
I volunteered to be yours
for the day.

08:20.369 --> 08:23.111
Uh, a chauffeur, that is.

08:23.154 --> 08:26.288
I am spoken for
by a Ms. Beatrice Mock.

08:26.331 --> 08:27.550
Yeah.

08:27.594 --> 08:29.813
We have been married
17 years this March,

08:29.857 --> 08:32.773
and, uh, if you need my

08:32.816 --> 08:34.818
qualifications
for this assignment,

08:34.862 --> 08:37.429
she can attest to my expertise

08:37.473 --> 08:40.737
in driving her, uh, crazy.

08:44.436 --> 08:47.004
You might want me to shut up.

08:47.048 --> 08:48.484
- Might.

08:48.528 --> 08:51.139
- Yeah.
A little hung?

08:51.182 --> 08:53.358
Well, just take a peek inside
that cooler to your left.

08:53.402 --> 08:56.797
I put a few cold beers
in there just in case.

09:05.545 --> 09:07.068
- You're a saint.

09:07.111 --> 09:10.158
- Oh, I always do that
on a funeral detail.

09:10.201 --> 09:12.334
First thing I do
when I get up in the morning,

09:12.377 --> 09:14.205
pop a few in the freezer.

09:14.249 --> 09:15.946
Get 'em good and cold.

09:15.990 --> 09:19.210
Lots of people, they just,
need a little something,

09:19.254 --> 09:20.211
to get 'em to a funeral.

09:20.255 --> 09:22.910
That is a sad thing.

09:22.953 --> 09:24.085
Funeral.

09:28.916 --> 09:32.180
Well, I will shut up now.

09:32.223 --> 09:33.485
- Thank you.

09:33.529 --> 09:35.052
- Uh, you mind if we just
stop by the station?

09:35.096 --> 09:37.141
There's something the chief
wants to bring you in on.

09:37.185 --> 09:39.361
♪

09:42.973 --> 09:46.586
[indistinct chatter]
[phone ringing]

09:46.629 --> 09:49.066
♪

09:49.110 --> 09:51.460
[indistinct radio chatter]

09:51.503 --> 09:53.897
- There she is.

09:53.941 --> 09:56.247
Dan, put your feet down.

09:56.291 --> 09:57.335
Hey.

09:57.379 --> 09:59.250
- We need to talk.

09:59.294 --> 10:00.338
Ferness called me.

10:00.382 --> 10:01.644
- What?
When?

10:01.688 --> 10:03.124
- Just now, this morning.

10:03.167 --> 10:04.604
He sounds desperate.

10:04.647 --> 10:06.518
- What'd he say?

10:06.562 --> 10:08.608
- That he didn't do it.

10:08.651 --> 10:10.261
- Oh, honey, they all say that.

10:10.305 --> 10:11.523
Even when they're scrubbing
the blood out

10:11.567 --> 10:12.655
from under their fingernails.

10:12.699 --> 10:14.918
- You need to do--
- Allegra.

10:14.962 --> 10:17.094
Trust us.
I'm gonna do my job today.

10:17.138 --> 10:19.096
All I ask is for you
to do yours.

10:21.490 --> 10:23.492
Mourn that sweet sister.

10:23.535 --> 10:27.104
And speaking of which,
reason I had Mock bring you by.

10:27.148 --> 10:30.804
Boys!
Meet Felicity's sister.

10:30.847 --> 10:33.154
Allegra Dill.

10:33.197 --> 10:34.242
Mock.

10:34.285 --> 10:35.373
- Mm?
Mm.

10:40.596 --> 10:41.858
- First time I saw Felicity,

10:41.902 --> 10:44.034
she was sitting
at that desk right there.

10:44.078 --> 10:45.732
It's my first day on the job,

10:45.775 --> 10:47.951
all my luggage is still
down in El Paso,

10:47.995 --> 10:49.779
and I thought I'd,
you know, drop by early,

10:49.823 --> 10:51.259
get a feel for the place.

10:51.302 --> 10:52.652
It was 8:30 a.m.

10:52.695 --> 10:54.828
I walk in and who do I see

10:54.871 --> 10:56.525
but this slip of a girl?

10:56.568 --> 10:58.745
Just sitting there,
working her way through

10:58.788 --> 11:00.921
a box of kung pao
and a mountain of paperwork.

11:00.964 --> 11:03.314
[all chuckling]

11:03.358 --> 11:06.013
Every single day,
Felicity damn Dill

11:06.056 --> 11:07.144
is sitting perky-assed
at that desk

11:07.188 --> 11:08.493
before I can even park my car.

11:08.537 --> 11:10.582
[laughter]

11:10.626 --> 11:12.976
So, finally, I figure I'm gonna
do something about it.

11:13.020 --> 11:16.023
So, 4:15 a.m., I march in,

11:16.066 --> 11:17.981
feeling like I got the jump
on this little

11:18.025 --> 11:21.376
brown-nosing flatfoot
can't find the time to go home.

11:23.204 --> 11:25.510
So, I walk in this room.
What do I see?

11:25.554 --> 11:28.470
Yep.
Officer Felicity Dill.

11:28.513 --> 11:31.386
She turns to me with that--
that innocent expression

11:31.429 --> 11:33.040
on that petite face,
and she says,

11:33.083 --> 11:34.737
"I know you like
to come in early, Chief,

11:34.781 --> 11:36.696
so I thought I'd make you
a cup of coffee.

11:36.739 --> 11:39.873
[laughter]

11:42.440 --> 11:43.398
Ain't that the tits?

11:43.441 --> 11:44.878
I know when I'm beat.

11:44.921 --> 11:47.010
That afternoon, I grabbed
Calvin Strucker and I said,

11:47.054 --> 11:48.838
"I want you to promote
that Dill girl

11:48.882 --> 11:50.840
just high as common sense
will let you."

11:50.884 --> 11:52.450
And he said, "Why?
'Cause she's good?"

11:52.494 --> 11:53.843
And I said, "Hell, no.

11:53.887 --> 11:55.236
'Cause she's a pain
in the ass!"

11:55.279 --> 11:58.239
[all laugh]

11:59.196 --> 12:01.808
- Yeah, that's right.
[laughs]

12:04.419 --> 12:06.290
- To Felicity Dill.

12:06.334 --> 12:09.467
May she be frustrating the shit
out of St. Peter in heaven.

12:09.511 --> 12:11.382
- That's right.

12:11.426 --> 12:13.558
[tender music]

12:13.602 --> 12:15.560
- Yep.

12:15.604 --> 12:21.001
♪

12:21.044 --> 12:24.787
[indistinct radio chatter]

12:28.617 --> 12:31.402
- What?

12:31.446 --> 12:33.883
- Just didn't know
she had a sister.

12:36.886 --> 12:39.846
♪

12:39.889 --> 12:41.456
- [exhales sharply]

12:44.764 --> 12:47.810
♪

12:47.854 --> 12:50.030
Long night?

12:50.073 --> 12:52.946
- Long week.
Have a seat.

12:59.213 --> 13:00.954
You sure you don't want to say
a few words today

13:00.997 --> 13:02.956
at the service?

13:02.999 --> 13:04.479
- Not my style.

13:06.655 --> 13:09.527
- I just thought maybe
you could add something,

13:09.571 --> 13:12.835
about her childhood
or your childhood.

13:12.879 --> 13:14.489
- What did she tell you?

13:16.360 --> 13:18.101
- Nothing.

13:18.145 --> 13:20.364
- Ever think there may have
been a reason for that?

13:23.498 --> 13:26.153
It wasn't like
what it was supposed to be.

13:28.329 --> 13:29.809
Our family.

13:29.852 --> 13:32.463
- How old were you
when they passed?

13:32.507 --> 13:34.378
- 17.

13:34.422 --> 13:35.423
Felicity was seven.

13:35.466 --> 13:37.947
- And you were responsible
for her?

13:37.991 --> 13:39.470
After the accident?

13:39.514 --> 13:42.082
- I did what I had to do.

13:42.125 --> 13:43.866
For the both of us.

13:43.910 --> 13:45.999
- And that was boarding school.

13:47.783 --> 13:50.394
- I didn't want her
to grow up here.

13:50.438 --> 13:51.787
But if she had,

13:51.831 --> 13:54.137
maybe she'd have had sense
enough not to come back.

13:54.181 --> 13:56.183
- Well, I'm sure
you did your best.

13:56.226 --> 13:59.447
But "anger gives
the devil a foothold."

13:59.490 --> 14:03.233
At least according
to this book right here.

14:10.762 --> 14:13.635
- Anger gives you a chance
to fucking survive.

14:15.767 --> 14:18.770
[indistinct muffled chatter]

14:18.814 --> 14:20.076
- Hear that?
He's at the high school.

14:20.120 --> 14:21.773
- You heard dispatch.
Let's get out of here.

14:21.817 --> 14:22.862
- All right, team, let's go.

14:22.905 --> 14:24.167
- High school?
- Yeah.

14:24.211 --> 14:27.257
- Can't wait to see his face
when we nail him.

14:27.301 --> 14:30.347
- We'll do our job,
You do yours.

14:30.391 --> 14:31.783
- The first guy gets shot at.

14:31.827 --> 14:34.482
- Floyd better be saying
his prayers.

14:38.181 --> 14:39.617
- Attention all units,
we have a visual

14:39.661 --> 14:40.880
on Floyd Ferness.

14:40.923 --> 14:44.144
Last spotted
at SD High football field.

14:44.187 --> 14:47.538
[dramatic music]

14:47.582 --> 14:52.500
♪

14:52.543 --> 14:55.459
[calm swing music]

14:55.503 --> 15:02.423
♪

15:10.997 --> 15:12.302
- So sorry.

15:12.346 --> 15:13.608
- Mm.

15:13.651 --> 15:16.437
- I'm so sorry, Allegra.
She was a good person.

15:16.480 --> 15:17.917
- Thank you, Lalo.

15:17.960 --> 15:19.875
- I'm sorry about your sister.

15:19.919 --> 15:21.224
And about the other day.

15:21.268 --> 15:23.835
- Oh, she had
the most angelic smile

15:23.879 --> 15:27.578
and beautiful blonde curls.

15:27.622 --> 15:29.145
Oh, come to think of it,

15:29.189 --> 15:31.756
that woman told me
her name was Francine.

15:31.800 --> 15:33.976
I-I'm sorry.
- I'm sorry.

15:34.020 --> 15:35.935
- I'm so sorry.

15:35.978 --> 15:38.981
[crowd chatter grows louder]

15:41.244 --> 15:43.725
- All right, come on.
- Oh, God.

15:47.294 --> 15:49.774
- Vultures, the lot of 'em.

15:49.818 --> 15:51.820
They feed on grief.

15:51.863 --> 15:54.605
The only solution
is make yourself

15:54.649 --> 15:56.781
unpalatable.

15:56.825 --> 15:59.654
Care to join me
in a little blood of Christ?

16:04.833 --> 16:06.704
[groans]

16:08.663 --> 16:09.969
- Thanks.

16:13.537 --> 16:15.409
What was that shit you pulled
with the mayor yesterday?

16:15.452 --> 16:17.280
- Hmm?
- Humiliating him?

16:17.324 --> 16:18.978
You angling for his job?

16:19.021 --> 16:20.588
- No, come on, Pick.

16:20.631 --> 16:23.983
Now, all that political stuff
can wait.

16:24.026 --> 16:26.202
This here is important.

16:30.032 --> 16:32.382
[clears throat]

16:32.426 --> 16:34.210
To Felicity.

16:34.254 --> 16:35.995
A sweet, sweet girl,

16:36.038 --> 16:41.174
and she would never, ever...

16:41.217 --> 16:43.132
stop following us.

16:43.176 --> 16:45.047
[both chuckle]

16:45.091 --> 16:47.789
Even when we took her
to the town dump.

16:47.832 --> 16:49.530
[chuckles]

16:52.750 --> 16:55.014
- Glad you're here.

16:55.057 --> 16:57.103
- Boss.
- Yo.

16:58.234 --> 17:00.802
Oh, hey.
The, uh, lawyer, right?

17:00.845 --> 17:02.847
- Oh, not today.
Just friend.

17:02.891 --> 17:05.024
- Well, then, friend,

17:05.067 --> 17:07.113
you've come to the right place.

17:08.853 --> 17:10.899
[coughs]

17:10.942 --> 17:12.683
There you go.
- Thank you.

17:12.727 --> 17:14.076
- Gotta.

17:14.120 --> 17:16.122
- Is he the only guard
you brought with you here?

17:17.775 --> 17:19.168
- Uh...

17:19.212 --> 17:22.041
Eliseo's the only one
who can wear my suits.

17:26.958 --> 17:30.049
Oh, well.
[laughs]

17:30.092 --> 17:33.530
Think I just
realized something.

17:33.574 --> 17:36.446
This must've been the room
he stole 'em out of.

17:37.839 --> 17:39.101
- Oh, my God.

17:39.145 --> 17:40.972
- [chuckles]

17:41.016 --> 17:42.626
[both laugh]

17:42.670 --> 17:45.194
- You're right.

17:45.238 --> 17:47.370
- Who stole what now?

17:47.414 --> 17:50.330
- Uh, about 20 years ago,
the good Mr. and Mrs. Dill

17:50.373 --> 17:51.853
went driving up to Colorado.

17:51.896 --> 17:53.159
- [sighs]

17:53.202 --> 17:55.291
- In search of
an investment opportunity.

17:55.335 --> 17:56.379
- It was a ghost town.

17:56.423 --> 17:58.729
A literal ghost town.

17:58.773 --> 17:59.991
For sale.
- Yeah.

18:00.035 --> 18:01.732
And what they found instead was

18:01.776 --> 18:04.953
the one corner on Earth
that Ambrose Dill couldn't cut.

18:04.996 --> 18:06.911
Out on Highway 21.

18:06.955 --> 18:08.522
90-yard drop.
[pops lips]

18:08.565 --> 18:11.046
Right over the side
of the mountain.

18:11.090 --> 18:12.656
- My God.

18:12.700 --> 18:14.267
I'm so sorry.
I didn't know that--

18:14.310 --> 18:15.877
- They said that Dad died
from the impact,

18:15.920 --> 18:17.879
but Mom died from relief.

18:17.922 --> 18:21.187
[both laugh]

18:21.230 --> 18:24.364
All of a sudden.

18:24.407 --> 18:26.322
I don't have to just finish
my calculus homework.

18:26.366 --> 18:27.715
I have to plan a funeral.

18:27.758 --> 18:30.413
- Oh, every two-bit
con artist, hack,

18:30.457 --> 18:33.416
and grifter south
of the panhandle showed up.

18:33.460 --> 18:35.288
There's this one
real extravagant fella

18:35.331 --> 18:37.507
named Chubb Hancock.

18:37.551 --> 18:41.207
And, uh, oh, he's just making
a show the whole time.

18:41.250 --> 18:43.600
Weeping and carrying on
during the service,

18:43.644 --> 18:47.300
so much so
that he had to excuse himself.

18:47.343 --> 18:50.433
- And he excused himself
right back here,

18:50.477 --> 18:52.609
where we had the ashes

18:52.653 --> 18:54.002
and the--
the pimento cheese sandwiches.

18:54.045 --> 18:55.438
- The cheese sandwiches.

18:55.482 --> 18:56.787
- Which he helped himself
to both.

18:56.831 --> 18:59.312
[both chuckling]

18:59.355 --> 19:01.183
- This man...

19:01.227 --> 19:03.272
stole your parents?

19:03.316 --> 19:05.796
- Ashes.
Both bags.

19:05.840 --> 19:07.972
I guess Dad had said
he'd pay Chubb the money

19:08.016 --> 19:09.757
he owed him over his dead body.

19:09.800 --> 19:13.021
So Chubb stood right over
that body and swiped it.

19:13.064 --> 19:14.153
And Mom's.

19:14.196 --> 19:16.546
[both chuckling]

19:16.590 --> 19:19.288
- That is a horrible story.

19:19.332 --> 19:22.161
- Oh, perspective, Counselor.

19:22.204 --> 19:24.119
Levity is a part of life.

19:24.163 --> 19:25.512
- Mm. Mm.

19:25.555 --> 19:28.210
- What was it you said
back there, Pick?

19:28.254 --> 19:31.300
Uh, about funerals
being too much fuss.

19:31.344 --> 19:34.564
- "The dead don't need 'em,

19:34.608 --> 19:36.827
and the living
don't deserve them."

19:36.871 --> 19:38.568
[both chuckle]

19:38.612 --> 19:40.004
Mm.

19:40.048 --> 19:42.398
I was 17 and...

19:44.226 --> 19:45.836
Furious.

19:48.187 --> 19:49.405
- And now?

19:49.449 --> 19:50.928
- Now I'm 38.

19:50.972 --> 19:53.757
[both chuckle]

19:53.801 --> 19:56.760
[organ playing]

19:56.804 --> 20:02.723
♪

20:10.557 --> 20:13.603
- She set aside her own fears

20:13.647 --> 20:16.215
so that she could
protect the innocent

20:16.258 --> 20:18.391
from those who sought
to harm them.

20:18.434 --> 20:20.175
In doing so,

20:20.219 --> 20:23.918
Detective Felicity Dill
reflected our highest ideals.

20:25.615 --> 20:29.010
On a personal note,
I would like to add that...

20:30.490 --> 20:34.015
Felicity was an exceptional
colleague and...

20:37.627 --> 20:39.716
And a...

20:39.760 --> 20:40.935
a good friend.

20:40.978 --> 20:42.850
- [clears throat loudly]

20:47.289 --> 20:49.683
- I will--
I will reflect upon our

20:49.726 --> 20:52.468
intimate conversations fondly

20:52.512 --> 20:55.297
in the days and years to come.

20:55.341 --> 20:56.994
We take comfort
in the knowledge

20:57.038 --> 21:00.563
that Felicity has finally
found peace in heaven.

21:00.607 --> 21:03.610
Reunited
with her loving parents...

21:05.002 --> 21:10.617
Ambrose and Isadora Dill.

21:15.839 --> 21:18.451
We hold Felicity in our hearts.

21:20.148 --> 21:24.935
Just as we hold
her only surviving relative.

21:24.979 --> 21:27.416
Allegra Dill,
you are not alone.

21:27.460 --> 21:30.245
The San Bonifacio
Police Department

21:30.289 --> 21:33.814
grieves with you
and stands by you.

21:33.857 --> 21:35.772
Today and always.

21:37.818 --> 21:40.734
Please rise and--
and join me for a hymn.

21:47.088 --> 21:50.004
[solemn music playing]

21:50.047 --> 21:54.356
♪

21:54.400 --> 21:57.141
- What's up?

21:57.185 --> 21:59.796
- I need some fresh air.

21:59.840 --> 22:06.586
all: ♪ Guide me,
oh, thou great redeemer ♪

22:06.629 --> 22:10.503
[music distorting]

22:10.546 --> 22:14.681
♪

22:19.555 --> 22:21.862
- You're early.
- So are you.

22:24.081 --> 22:26.127
Brattle wants to come in.

22:26.170 --> 22:27.520
- Immunity might be tricky.

22:27.563 --> 22:30.871
- He's willing to do time.

22:33.047 --> 22:35.745
- Well, well, well.
That is a curveball.

22:35.789 --> 22:36.920
- There's nothing in his file

22:36.964 --> 22:38.574
that suggests
he'd be open to this.

22:38.618 --> 22:40.750
- What changed?

22:40.794 --> 22:43.840
- Assuming he's not bluffing?

22:43.884 --> 22:45.233
Well, for one,

22:45.276 --> 22:46.756
I think he's trying
to ratfuck Jake.

22:46.800 --> 22:49.498
- A given.
And for two?

22:49.542 --> 22:51.108
- I think he's tired.

22:51.152 --> 22:52.501
- Did he say as much?

22:52.545 --> 22:54.024
- He's living in a van, Cyrus.

22:54.068 --> 22:56.505
He drove me
to an abandoned slaughterhouse.

22:56.549 --> 22:58.246
It was full of drones.

22:58.289 --> 23:00.466
- How many?

23:00.509 --> 23:02.032
- At least two dozen.

23:04.121 --> 23:06.080
- Livestock?

23:06.123 --> 23:07.821
The slaughterhouse.
What did it process?

23:07.864 --> 23:09.039
- Beef.

23:09.083 --> 23:10.084
- Mm.

23:11.564 --> 23:13.696
Unmanned drones
suggests drug smuggling.

23:13.740 --> 23:16.003
That's not Brattle.
Or Spivey, for that matter.

23:16.046 --> 23:19.136
- I think he was trying
to send me a message.

23:19.180 --> 23:22.009
He mentioned Al-Namur.

23:22.052 --> 23:25.534
It's a village
about 45 miles south of Aleppo.

23:25.578 --> 23:27.318
They grow figs.

23:27.362 --> 23:29.320
- Mmm.

23:29.364 --> 23:30.452
- Forget about the figs.

23:30.496 --> 23:31.758
- I'll look into it.

23:31.801 --> 23:34.021
In the meantime, you try
and meet with him again.

23:35.588 --> 23:36.850
- You're not
seriously considering

23:36.893 --> 23:39.940
doing a deal
with Brattle, are you?

23:39.983 --> 23:40.854
He's a savage.

23:40.897 --> 23:43.639
- Allegra, don't be squeamish.

23:43.683 --> 23:45.641
- Cyrus,
tell the FBI he's here.

23:45.685 --> 23:48.470
Or at least let me speak
to the senator about it.

23:48.514 --> 23:50.646
- We both know
that's not a good idea.

23:50.690 --> 23:52.343
♪

23:52.387 --> 23:53.823
- Brattle is the target.

23:53.867 --> 23:56.652
He has been
since you put me on this.

23:56.696 --> 23:58.393
Don't switch it up now.

23:58.437 --> 24:00.526
- The hearing is imminent,
and Spivey is stalling.

24:00.569 --> 24:02.745
- Cyrus, God damn it.

24:02.789 --> 24:04.747
I already offered
Jake the deal.

24:04.791 --> 24:07.054
He won't talk
until Brattle is in custody.

24:07.097 --> 24:10.231
What am I supposed
to tell him now?

24:10.274 --> 24:11.928
- You tell him nothing.

24:11.972 --> 24:14.104
Not about this or anything
relating to our business.

24:14.148 --> 24:16.150
You walk into the church.
You dab your eyes.

24:16.193 --> 24:17.368
You mourn your loss.

24:17.412 --> 24:19.240
And you will await
further instructions.

24:19.283 --> 24:20.894
- This is horseshit.

24:20.937 --> 24:22.765
- Here.

24:22.809 --> 24:24.550
Fake it if you have to.

24:26.987 --> 24:29.816
Don't let these people see
what you really are.

24:31.034 --> 24:35.952
♪

24:38.346 --> 24:40.957
- That was a great speech, bud.

24:41.001 --> 24:43.003
- It wasn't a speech.
It was a eulogy.

24:43.046 --> 24:46.180
- Cool.
Did you rehearse it or...

24:46.223 --> 24:47.616
- That's not how this works.

24:47.660 --> 24:49.662
- Got it.
Got it!

24:49.705 --> 24:51.620
So that was the first time
in the room?

24:51.664 --> 24:54.101
Oh, man.
You killed it, bro!

24:54.144 --> 24:56.495
Killed it!

24:56.538 --> 24:58.801
Word choice.
My bad.

24:58.845 --> 25:00.760
- Oh, hell, yeah,
we were close.

25:00.803 --> 25:02.631
We were real close.

25:02.675 --> 25:04.720
We talked just about every day.

25:04.764 --> 25:07.767
In fact, I'm the last one
she talked to before...

25:08.811 --> 25:10.421
[imitates explosion]

25:10.465 --> 25:12.336
You know?

25:12.380 --> 25:16.123
She thought of me as someone
she could confide in.

25:16.166 --> 25:21.563
I just wish she hadn't kept
so much bottled up inside.

25:21.607 --> 25:25.959
Human connection
is such a gift.

25:26.002 --> 25:28.527
- Well, that doesn't
sound right.

25:28.570 --> 25:30.180
[organ music playing]

25:30.224 --> 25:31.312
- What part?

25:31.355 --> 25:33.532
- So, you were her lawyer?

25:33.575 --> 25:35.577
- I was.

25:35.621 --> 25:37.536
I was also her friend.

25:39.668 --> 25:41.801
- Are you allowed to be both?

25:43.411 --> 25:45.631
- Don't tell anybody.

25:45.674 --> 25:47.807
- Okay.
[laughs]

25:49.243 --> 25:51.375
- You know, I'm surprised
we've never met.

25:51.419 --> 25:54.857
You know I practically helped
raise Felicity, you know?

25:54.901 --> 25:57.294
Yeah, bought her first
fishing rod, first Barbie.

25:57.338 --> 26:00.602
Well, the Barbie I stole,
but yeah.

26:00.646 --> 26:02.299
Anyway, I figured
since your wife

26:02.343 --> 26:03.779
was at my house yesterday,

26:03.823 --> 26:05.955
I might come over
and introduce myself.

26:05.999 --> 26:08.479
- My wife was at your house?

26:08.523 --> 26:10.917
- Oh, well, come on now.

26:10.960 --> 26:13.441
You can't exactly hide a little
firecracker like that away.

26:13.484 --> 26:14.703
Am I right?
Huh?

26:14.747 --> 26:16.662
I mean, hell, not even today.

26:16.705 --> 26:18.141
- Wait, she's here--

26:18.185 --> 26:21.275
- Oh, she's over by
the sacristy making small talk.

26:21.318 --> 26:22.842
Ooh, boy.

26:22.885 --> 26:27.237
Oh, but I tell you,
she is fine.

26:27.281 --> 26:28.456
Respect.

26:28.499 --> 26:30.327
- Excuse me.

26:30.371 --> 26:32.199
- You're excused, Captain.

26:47.083 --> 26:48.781
[sighs]

26:59.705 --> 27:02.838
[birds chirping]

27:15.764 --> 27:19.115
- I just needed some fresh air.

27:19.159 --> 27:21.857
Can I have one of those?
[chuckles]

27:31.345 --> 27:32.912
Thank you.

27:39.701 --> 27:42.182
- Do you smoke?

27:42.225 --> 27:43.662
- No.

27:49.406 --> 27:50.886
[sighs]

27:53.715 --> 27:55.369
Funerals are hard.

27:58.546 --> 28:00.766
I went to my mother's.

28:00.809 --> 28:04.073
14 years old, stoned,
in goth makeup.

28:04.117 --> 28:06.293
But I went.
[laughs]

28:10.993 --> 28:12.473
It's about the only place
in the entire world

28:12.516 --> 28:13.996
you don't want to be,
but it's the place

28:14.040 --> 28:17.434
the entire world expects
to find you.

28:17.478 --> 28:18.871
Front and center.

28:21.569 --> 28:23.223
So I get it.

28:26.705 --> 28:28.358
And I'm sorry.

28:32.406 --> 28:33.886
- Thanks.

28:40.719 --> 28:43.025
- I know it's odd.

28:43.069 --> 28:45.375
But I had to come.
I'm worried about Gene.

28:45.419 --> 28:47.508
He just loved her so much,
you know?

28:47.551 --> 28:48.509
[fly buzzes]

28:48.552 --> 28:50.032
[blows air]

28:54.080 --> 28:56.082
I think it's probably good

28:56.125 --> 28:57.866
to be able to love
more than one person.

28:57.910 --> 28:59.346
[scoffs]
I wish I could.

28:59.389 --> 29:01.174
[chuckles]

29:01.217 --> 29:03.263
- Lucretia,
you shouldn't be here.

29:03.306 --> 29:04.743
♪

29:04.786 --> 29:07.789
- But here I am.

29:07.833 --> 29:10.574
- Is she bothering you?

29:10.618 --> 29:13.577
- No.

29:13.621 --> 29:14.840
- I'm not a bother, Gene.

29:14.883 --> 29:17.799
Don't treat me
like I'm a bother.

29:17.843 --> 29:20.106
- Excuse us.

29:21.760 --> 29:27.853
♪

29:27.896 --> 29:29.724
- What is that?

29:29.768 --> 29:31.421
♪

29:31.465 --> 29:32.771
- Dill.

29:36.818 --> 29:38.907
- Freddie Laffter.

29:38.951 --> 29:40.256
- We're going with the stuff

29:40.300 --> 29:42.693
about your sister's
insurance policy.

29:42.737 --> 29:44.739
And the money sunk into
the apartment building,

29:44.783 --> 29:47.133
all that crap.

29:47.176 --> 29:49.570
Any comment you want to make?

29:49.613 --> 29:52.268
- No.
No comment, Chuckles.

29:52.312 --> 29:53.356
Nothing.

29:55.358 --> 29:58.709
- I heard some of what
the boyfriend said in there.

29:58.753 --> 30:02.365
Awfully pious for an adulterer.

30:02.409 --> 30:04.280
Made her sound
like some kind of saint.

30:04.324 --> 30:05.934
- And she wasn't?

30:05.978 --> 30:07.414
- That a question
or a statement?

30:09.677 --> 30:11.244
[chuckles]

30:11.287 --> 30:14.247
I know you've got doubts too,
Dill.

30:14.290 --> 30:16.031
You can hate me all you want,

30:16.075 --> 30:19.078
but we're the only ones

30:19.121 --> 30:20.819
that see it plain.

30:22.646 --> 30:25.562
[organ music playing]

30:25.606 --> 30:26.912
♪

30:26.955 --> 30:28.522
- All I see is a sick old man

30:28.565 --> 30:31.264
who's getting a sneak preview
of what's around the corner.

30:31.307 --> 30:32.395
- [chuckles]

30:34.658 --> 30:37.009
Even the cops weren't
sure about her.

30:38.706 --> 30:41.927
Word has it that she got
into a screaming match

30:41.970 --> 30:45.844
with Strucker,
her would-be father figure.

30:45.887 --> 30:47.933
- About?

30:47.976 --> 30:49.935
- Well, apparently,
young Detective Dill

30:49.978 --> 30:51.893
couldn't keep her nose
out of Packingtown.

30:51.937 --> 30:54.374
Even after he took her
off the beat.

30:54.417 --> 30:55.897
♪

30:55.941 --> 30:57.029
- When was this?

30:57.072 --> 30:58.639
- Three weeks ago.

30:58.682 --> 31:01.555
Around the same time
she took out that policy

31:01.598 --> 31:04.166
making you, what,
the second richest person

31:04.210 --> 31:06.821
to ever come out
of the old neighborhood?

31:06.865 --> 31:09.519
After your jarhead pal,
of course.

31:09.563 --> 31:12.696
- Don't print anything
you can't verify, Freddie.

31:12.740 --> 31:14.176
- Please.

31:14.220 --> 31:17.440
All of this shit
is unverifiable.

31:17.484 --> 31:19.921
The dead are just clay
for the living

31:19.965 --> 31:22.184
to mold and shape
into whatever makes them

31:22.228 --> 31:23.925
sleep better at night.

31:23.969 --> 31:25.492
♪

31:25.535 --> 31:26.623
Speaking of which,

31:26.667 --> 31:29.061
how are you sleeping
at night, Dill?

31:29.104 --> 31:32.238
♪

31:32.281 --> 31:34.501
Hmm.

31:34.544 --> 31:36.372
I thought so.

31:38.113 --> 31:41.073
[dramatic music]

31:41.116 --> 31:44.206
♪

31:48.297 --> 31:49.951
- It's breadknife weather.

31:52.432 --> 31:53.215
- Come again?

31:53.259 --> 31:54.782
- It's breadknife weather.

31:54.825 --> 31:56.523
What Felicity used to call it.

31:56.566 --> 31:57.828
Soon as it hit
the triple digits,

31:57.872 --> 32:00.179
she knew she'd be busy.

32:00.222 --> 32:01.397
People in this town?

32:01.441 --> 32:02.877
When you crank the burner
this high,

32:02.921 --> 32:04.923
they don't even bother
reaching for the pointy stuff

32:04.966 --> 32:07.186
before they start
stabbing each other.

32:07.229 --> 32:08.404
- Yeah, that sounds like her.

32:08.448 --> 32:10.580
- [chuckles]
Sure does!

32:10.624 --> 32:12.060
- Sergeant Mock.

32:12.104 --> 32:15.194
Did my sister and Strucker
have a falling out?

32:15.237 --> 32:20.025
- Uh, well, um,
a family quarrel, more like.

32:20.068 --> 32:22.592
Yeah, about three weeks ago.

32:22.636 --> 32:25.291
Um, and Calvin,

32:25.334 --> 32:27.815
uh, he must've been
awful sore about...

32:27.858 --> 32:31.253
- Are you working right now?

32:31.297 --> 32:33.038
- Are you seriously telling me

32:33.081 --> 32:34.604
you're buying
what they're selling?

32:34.648 --> 32:36.128
- This is not a transaction,
Allegra.

32:36.171 --> 32:37.564
People mourn in different ways.

32:37.607 --> 32:40.219
- You think Floyd Ferness
killed her?

32:40.262 --> 32:42.699
- I think today it doesn't
matter who killed her.

32:42.743 --> 32:45.006
I think what matters
is that she's dead.

32:47.791 --> 32:49.184
We've got to accept that.

32:49.228 --> 32:51.708
- They don't get to decide
who she was.

32:51.752 --> 32:53.972
They don't get to have her.

32:55.538 --> 32:57.976
- The funeral is not
for Felicity.

33:00.065 --> 33:01.980
It's for the people
who loved her.

33:02.023 --> 33:03.242
To bring closure.

33:03.285 --> 33:04.721
- I don't want closure.

33:04.765 --> 33:07.681
[dramatic piano music]

33:07.724 --> 33:08.943
[can lid pops]

33:08.987 --> 33:11.902
[aggressive electronic music]

33:11.946 --> 33:14.862
[upbeat rock music]

33:14.905 --> 33:22.000
♪

33:29.094 --> 33:32.053
- My grandmother's gravesite
is right over here.

33:32.097 --> 33:34.534
I'ma pay her a quick visit.

33:34.577 --> 33:38.277
♪

33:40.192 --> 33:42.281
- You come here often?

33:45.719 --> 33:47.155
- Why, do you?

33:48.722 --> 33:51.029
- Oh, I visit Daddy.

33:51.072 --> 33:53.379
Every month or so.

33:53.422 --> 33:57.035
I figure since he gave me
the silent treatment

33:57.078 --> 34:00.212
most of my childhood,

34:00.255 --> 34:02.779
there's time enough
to return the favor.

34:02.823 --> 34:05.043
[somber piano music]

34:05.086 --> 34:06.870
- What was she doing here,
Jake?

34:06.914 --> 34:10.004
She had to come back
to this poisonous shithole.

34:10.048 --> 34:13.399
- Poisonous shithole would look
good on a postcard, I admit,

34:13.442 --> 34:16.880
but, you know, she and I
had another word for it.

34:16.924 --> 34:18.621
- Don't.

34:18.665 --> 34:20.884
- It's home.

34:20.928 --> 34:22.712
- [sighs]

34:24.453 --> 34:26.629
- You ought to give her
more credit, Pick.

34:26.673 --> 34:29.763
She really wanted
to fix this place.

34:29.806 --> 34:32.853
♪

34:32.896 --> 34:37.205
When's the last time
you actually saw Felicity?

34:39.077 --> 34:41.122
- Three years ago.

34:41.166 --> 34:42.471
In D.C.

34:42.515 --> 34:44.212
- Mm-hmm.

34:44.256 --> 34:45.953
And how was that?

34:45.996 --> 34:47.389
- It was fine.

34:47.433 --> 34:49.304
- Pick, how fine
could it have been

34:49.348 --> 34:52.002
if you never saw her again?

34:52.046 --> 34:54.614
- I didn't ask her to come.

34:54.657 --> 34:57.704
She...

34:57.747 --> 35:02.056
heard something in my voice,
I guess.

35:02.100 --> 35:03.927
- How bad was it?

35:03.971 --> 35:04.928
- Bad.

35:04.972 --> 35:07.235
♪

35:07.279 --> 35:08.889
The senator was on
finance then,

35:08.932 --> 35:13.981
and I was investigating a guy
for insider training.

35:14.024 --> 35:15.635
And I pushed too hard.

35:18.116 --> 35:21.641
He didn't want to take
the fall.

35:21.684 --> 35:25.471
So he took a swan dive off of
a ninth-story building instead.

35:27.212 --> 35:28.213
- Ouch.

35:28.256 --> 35:29.953
- And then one night,

35:29.997 --> 35:32.130
there was a knock on the door.

35:32.173 --> 35:34.436
And that's Felicity.

35:34.480 --> 35:36.612
- That sounds nice.

35:36.656 --> 35:39.180
- She got me back on my feet.

35:39.224 --> 35:40.268
And at the end of three days,

35:40.312 --> 35:43.576
I started walking
and talking again.

35:43.619 --> 35:47.057
Went to the movies,
even laughed a little.

35:47.101 --> 35:48.711
And then she was gone.

35:51.932 --> 35:54.152
It wasn't special.
It wasn't anything.

35:55.588 --> 35:58.982
- Christ.

35:59.026 --> 36:01.159
I get it now.

36:01.202 --> 36:03.161
You must have hated that.

36:03.204 --> 36:04.858
Hated her for it.

36:06.251 --> 36:08.688
♪

36:08.731 --> 36:10.385
Well, Felicity
taking care of you

36:10.429 --> 36:14.215
when it's supposed to be
the other way around.

36:14.259 --> 36:16.826
[gunshots fire]

36:16.870 --> 36:19.307
- Ready, aim, fire.

36:19.351 --> 36:20.961
[gunshots fire]
- [mutters indistinctly]

36:21.004 --> 36:22.223
[high-pitched ringing]

36:22.267 --> 36:23.920
Pick!

36:28.838 --> 36:31.798
["Taps" playing]

36:31.841 --> 36:36.846
♪

36:36.890 --> 36:41.024
[camera shutter clicking]

36:41.068 --> 36:42.678
[music distorting]

36:42.722 --> 36:46.029
- Would you like to say
some final words?

36:46.073 --> 36:47.944
[voice echoing]

36:47.988 --> 36:50.947
[tense music]

36:50.991 --> 36:55.561
♪

36:55.604 --> 36:57.171
Allegra.

36:57.215 --> 37:00.174
- I remember now.

37:00.218 --> 37:02.437
- Allegra.

37:12.404 --> 37:14.406
[mic feedback whines]

37:16.234 --> 37:17.278
[feedback drones]

37:17.322 --> 37:19.498
- Uh, hi, uh...

37:19.541 --> 37:21.978
[camera shutter clicking]

37:22.022 --> 37:23.371
I'm A.D. Singe.

37:23.415 --> 37:25.243
Like "Scorch."

37:25.286 --> 37:26.331
[tense music]

37:26.374 --> 37:29.290
Uh, I'm a good friend--

37:29.334 --> 37:31.640
I was a good friend
of Felicity's.

37:31.684 --> 37:32.902
- No.

37:32.946 --> 37:34.295
No.

37:34.339 --> 37:36.297
No. No.

37:37.777 --> 37:39.474
[crowd murmuring]

37:41.824 --> 37:44.827
[grunting]

37:47.352 --> 37:49.267
What...

37:49.310 --> 37:52.618
[grunts loudly]
Come on.

37:52.661 --> 37:54.054
What...

37:54.097 --> 37:56.578
[grunts]

37:56.622 --> 37:59.755
[triumphant music]

37:59.799 --> 38:02.192
♪

38:02.236 --> 38:05.457
[singers vocalizing]

38:05.500 --> 38:10.113
♪

38:10.157 --> 38:13.682
[Niño Bravo's "Mi Tierra"]

38:13.726 --> 38:18.165
- ♪ Mi tierra tiene palmeras

38:18.208 --> 38:19.297
♪ Como

38:20.863 --> 38:25.825
- [laughing]

38:50.023 --> 38:51.981
Fliss.

38:52.025 --> 38:53.679
God damn you.

38:57.944 --> 39:00.294
Why'd you have to go
and die on me?

39:00.338 --> 39:03.384
[breathing heavily]

39:07.127 --> 39:09.521
Fuck you for making me
come back here.

39:15.309 --> 39:17.093
You dummy.

39:31.456 --> 39:33.893
No one should ever
have to be alone here.

39:37.549 --> 39:39.159
- Who are you talking to?

39:39.202 --> 39:40.856
- Whoa!

39:41.857 --> 39:43.163
Oh.

39:43.206 --> 39:45.252
[suspenseful music]

39:45.295 --> 39:48.342
- Here.
Keep this somewhere safe.

39:48.386 --> 39:49.517
- Is this...

39:49.561 --> 39:51.301
- It's the recording.

39:51.345 --> 39:53.086
From Felicity's apartment.

39:55.523 --> 39:57.395
I think it'll tell you
who killed her.

39:57.438 --> 39:58.961
- You didn't listen to it?

39:59.005 --> 40:00.746
- Nah, it was encrypted.

40:00.789 --> 40:02.138
Only one with the key is--

40:02.182 --> 40:03.444
- Harold Snow.

40:03.488 --> 40:06.839
- Yeah, I couldn't get to him.
Never had a chance.

40:06.882 --> 40:08.754
[laughs]

40:08.797 --> 40:10.930
Guess I'm used to that.

40:13.454 --> 40:16.239
♪

40:16.283 --> 40:17.458
You need to scream now.

40:17.502 --> 40:19.417
♪

40:19.460 --> 40:21.114
- What?

40:21.157 --> 40:23.072
- I need you to scream.

40:23.116 --> 40:25.074
- What?
No!

40:25.118 --> 40:27.033
No!

40:27.076 --> 40:29.296
- This needs to look real.
- Freeze!

40:29.339 --> 40:30.602
- They can't know
I gave it to you.

40:30.645 --> 40:32.473
- Don't you move, Floyd!

40:32.517 --> 40:34.083
Let go of her now!
Let go of her now!

40:34.127 --> 40:35.433
- Oh, shit.

40:35.476 --> 40:36.651
- [screams]

40:36.695 --> 40:39.437
- Don't do this, Floyd.

40:39.480 --> 40:41.439
Take your hands off her now!

40:41.482 --> 40:43.571
- [screams]
- Move, move! Go!

40:43.615 --> 40:44.790
- Shit! Come on!

40:44.833 --> 40:46.661
- Floyd, listen to me.

40:46.705 --> 40:48.184
You were right about Felicity.

40:48.228 --> 40:49.621
Okay, she got herself
into something

40:49.664 --> 40:50.752
that she shouldn't have.

40:50.796 --> 40:52.493
Strucker figured it out,

40:52.537 --> 40:54.234
and that's why
they were targets.

40:54.277 --> 40:55.975
- Get the perimeter, go!

40:56.018 --> 40:57.803
♪

40:57.846 --> 40:59.500
- I know it wasn't you.

40:59.544 --> 41:01.459
It doesn't have to go this way.

41:01.502 --> 41:03.461
It doesn't.

41:03.504 --> 41:04.853
- It's already gone.

41:04.897 --> 41:06.420
- I don't want
to do this, Floyd.

41:06.464 --> 41:07.639
Don't make me do this.

41:07.682 --> 41:09.467
[crowd screaming]

41:09.510 --> 41:10.946
- It's fine.
It's fine.

41:10.990 --> 41:12.078
It's fine.

41:12.121 --> 41:13.645
- Figure this out, okay?
- No, please!

41:13.688 --> 41:15.298
[groans]
No!

41:15.342 --> 41:17.605
- Stop!
- Floyd!

41:17.649 --> 41:18.911
- Hands off to Ferness,
and he's hit,

41:18.954 --> 41:20.782
but he's still on his feet!

41:20.826 --> 41:22.305
He's at the 40!
Nobody can run at him!

41:22.349 --> 41:24.003
30! 15!

41:24.046 --> 41:26.484
[gunshots firing]

41:30.488 --> 41:32.315
[gunshot fires]

41:32.359 --> 41:33.665
[body thumps]

41:34.666 --> 41:37.320
♪

41:37.364 --> 41:39.148
- [breathing heavily]

41:39.192 --> 41:42.195
[Sharon Jones & the Dap Kings'
"Just Give Me Your Time"]

41:42.238 --> 41:45.590
[singer vocalizing]

41:45.633 --> 41:48.027
- He's gone.

41:48.070 --> 41:54.990
♪

41:55.034 --> 41:58.559
- ♪ I don't need
your promises ♪

41:58.603 --> 42:00.605
♪ I don't need your lies

42:00.648 --> 42:02.476
- We got one.
Floyd Ferness.

42:02.520 --> 42:05.392
- ♪ I don't need your tears

42:05.435 --> 42:09.439
[voice slowing down]
♪ I don't need your sighs

42:09.483 --> 42:11.180
♪ Just call me your baby

42:11.224 --> 42:14.923
♪ And I'll love you
over again ♪

42:14.967 --> 42:18.753
♪ Just give me your time

42:21.234 --> 42:25.586
[at normal speed]
♪ I'm outside your door

42:25.630 --> 42:28.937
♪ I don't mind the rain

42:28.981 --> 42:31.723
♪ I'm just waiting
and waiting and waiting ♪

42:31.766 --> 42:35.640
♪ For an end to this pain

42:35.683 --> 42:41.297
♪ Just let me in, baby,
and I'll love you over again ♪
